HEADWORD: Seducement
<hw>Se*duce"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of seducing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The means employed to seduce, as flattery, promises,
deception, etc.; arts of enticing or corrupting.</def>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seducer</ent>⟦br⟧
